 r←GetUserHomPath;os
⍝ Returns the user's HOME path on the current operating system, like
⍝ /home/<⎕an>  on Linux
 :Select os←APLTreeUtils2.GetOperatingSystem ⍬
 :Case 'Win'
     r←¯1↓⊃1 ⎕NPARTS ¯1↓⊃1 ⎕NPARTS 2⊃4070⌶0
 :Case 'Lin'
     r←'/home/',⎕AN
 :Case 'Mac'
     r←'/Users/',⎕AN
 :Else
     ('<',os,'> is not a supported operating system')⎕SIGNAL 11
 :EndSelect
